        <div n="124-345B" type="poem"><head type="note" n="1" xml:id="spp-124-345B-headnote-1"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-124-345B-headnote-1-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-124-345B-headnote-1-line-group-1-line-1">Tatler vol. 1 p. \lost in gutter\</l></lg></head><head type="note" n="2" xml:id="spp-124-345B-headnote-2"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-124-345B-headnote-2-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-124-345B-headnote-2-line-group-1-line-1"/></lg></head><head type="note" n="3" xml:id="spp-124-345B-headnote-3"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-124-345B-headnote-3-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-124-345B-headnote-3-line-group-1-line-1"/></lg></head>
      <lg n="1" type="stanza"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-124-345B-line-1"> How hardly here &amp; there an hackney-Coach&#13;</l><l n="2" xml:id="spp-124-345B-line-2"> Appearing, shew'd y<hi rend="sup">e</hi> ruddy morn's approach.</l><l n="3" xml:id="spp-124-345B-line-3"> Now Betty From her Master's bed had flown,</l><l n="4" xml:id="spp-124-345B-line-4"> And Softly Stole to discompose her own.</l><l n="5" xml:id="spp-124-345B-line-5"> The Slipshod 'Prentice from his Masters door,</l><l n="6" xml:id="spp-124-345B-line-6"> Had par'd y<hi rend="sup">e</hi> Street, &amp; sprinkled round y<hi rend="sup">e</hi> floor.</l><l n="7" xml:id="spp-124-345B-line-7"> Now Moll had whirl'd her Mop w<hi rend="sup">tḥ</hi> dextrous Airs,</l><l n="8" xml:id="spp-124-345B-line-8"> Prepar'd to Scrub y<hi rend="sup">e</hi> entry &amp; y<hi rend="sup">e</hi> Stairs.</l><l n="9" xml:id="spp-124-345B-line-9"> The Youth w<hi rend="sup">tḥ</hi> broomy Stumps began to trace</l><l n="10" xml:id="spp-124-345B-line-10"> The kennel edge, where wheels had worn y<hi rend="sup">e</hi> place.</l><l n="11" xml:id="spp-124-345B-line-11"> The Small-Coal man was heard w<hi rend="sup">tḥ</hi> cadence deep,</l><l n="12" xml:id="spp-124-345B-line-12"> 'Til drown'd in shriller notes of Chimney-sweep.</l><l n="13" xml:id="spp-124-345B-line-13"> Duns at his Lordship's Gate began to meet,</l><l n="14" xml:id="spp-124-345B-line-14"> And brick-dust Moll had scream'd thro' half a street.</l><l n="15" xml:id="spp-124-345B-line-15"> The Turn·key now his flock returning Sees,</l><l n="16" xml:id="spp-124-345B-line-16"> Duly let out for Nighto returning fees.</l><l n="17" xml:id="spp-124-345B-line-17"> The Watchful Bailiffs take their Silent stands</l><l n="18" xml:id="spp-124-345B-line-18"> And Schoolboys lag with Satchels in their hands.124-345B   </l></lg></div>
